result.execSummary:
The defendant Donna M Fleury was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Forgery [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] case called at 9:35am. 
Defendant Donna M Fleury in court, in custody, with Attorney Sylvie Dahnert.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
The Court reviews the Criminal Case Settlement form with Ms. Fleury, verifying with her that she understands and joins in the agreement.
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " Guilty " entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Fleury guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2.  Further, the Court reads-in an uncharged referral for Felony Bailumping related to a 6/16/15 Escape from the Walworth County Jail, and bars further prosecution of this referral.


On Count #1, the Court sentences Ms. Fleury to 4  years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  1 year, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 3 years.  This sentence is consecutive to any previously imposed sentence.    
The Court finds that Ms. Fleury is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that Ms. Fleury is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
 The Court gives  0  days credit for time already served.

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with treatment recommendation as required by the Agent
--to any other undergo assessment, treatment, counseling or therapy as required by the Agent
--to be subject to random drug and/or alcohol screening, this screening is to occur at least two times a month for the first six months after release from custody, and thereafter as frequently as the Agent deems appropriate
--to obtain/maintain gainful employment and/or educational programming as approved by the Agent
--no possession of any illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia
--no contact with Jose D Gonzalez Jr.
--to make restitution of $41.20 to Jose Gonzalez Jr.
--to maintain absolute sobriety: no possess or consumption of alcohol
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--no possession of dangerous weapons
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision
--to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge
